            , informing me that the prisoner had made his escape, and ordering me to make diligent search after him; I took him the next day at Manchester, making a woman's shoe.</p>
               <p>PRISONER's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>When I came from on board of ship, I did it for fear of my life; there were twelve of us upon deck, and one Smith threatened to cut every one's throat that would not go into the boat, and come on shore. I went down to Manchester to follow my business.</p>
